      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De amicitia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e112">Cum quis in prosperitate diligitur, incertum est
              valde, utrum prosperitas, an persona diligatur; amissio autem felicitatis interrogat
              vim dilectionis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e127">Qui ex adversitate proximum despicit, aperte
              convincitur, quod hunc in prosperis non amavit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Dialogis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e142">Inter amantes se amicos, magnum charitatis
              familiaritas ausum praebet.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Pastorali</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e157">Ab illo, qui summe rectus est, eo ipso jam
              discrepat, quo perversorum amicitiis vita nostra concordat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e173">Amicorum amissio nos tanto debet tolerabilius
              contristare, quanto amissuros nos illos conditio mortalis exposcit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>)</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e188">Ut aliquid saecularis auctoritatis loquar, cum
              amicis omnia tractanda sunt, sed prius de ipsis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e195">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e203">Nemo potest diligere, quos non vult
              videre.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e210">Isidorus, in <title>Etymologiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e218">Amicus, quasi <!--<i>-->animi<!--</i>--> vel
              <!--<i>-->amicitiae<!--</i>--> custos per derivationem, dictus autem proprie amicus ab
              <!--<i>-->hamo<!--</i>-->, id est a catena charitatis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e235">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e245" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e237">Isidorus, <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e245">Non sunt fideles in amicitia, quos munus, non
              gratia copulat: hi cito deserunt, nisi semper acceperint. Dilectio enim, quae munere
              glutinatur, eo suspenso dissolvitur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e250">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e260" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e252">Augustinus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e260">Nemo potest veraciter amicus esse hominis, nisi
              fuerit ipsius primitus veritatis: quod si gratis non fiat, nullo fieri pacto
              potest.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e266">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e276" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e268">Augustinus, <title>de Catechizandis Rudibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e276">Nulla est major ad amorem invitatio, quam
              praevenire amando. Et nimis durus est animus, qui dilectionem si nolebat impendere,
              noluit rependere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e281">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e291" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e283">Augustinus, in <title>Soliloquiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e291">Illam amicitiae legem justissimam esse arbitror,
              qua praescribitur, ut non minus, ita nec plus quis amicum, quam seipsum
              diligat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e296">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e306" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e298">Augustinus, in <title>Soliloquiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e306">Tanto magis amo amicos meos, quanto magis bene
              utuntur anima rationali, vel certe quantum desiderant ea bene uti.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e311">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e321" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e313">Ambrosius, <title>de Officiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e321">Pietatis custos amicitia est, et aequalitatis
              magistra, ut superior inferiori se exhibeat aequalem, et inferior superiori
              fidelem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e326">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e336" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e328">Ambrosius, <title>de Officiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e336">Amicitia nescit superbiam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e341">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e351" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e343">Ambrosius, <title>de Officiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e351">Virtus est amicitia, non quaestus: non pecunia
              paratur, sed gratia: non pollicitatione pretiorum, sed concertatione
              benevolentiae.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e357">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e367" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e359">Joannes Chrysostomus, <title>de Compunctione</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e367">Ubi amicitia permanet, nihil facile creditur,
              nil facile recipitur, quod dissidium possit operari.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e372">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e382" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e374">Hieronymus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e382">In amicis non res quaeritur, sed voluntas; quia
              alterum et ab inimicis saepe praebetur, alterum sola charitas tribuit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e387">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e397" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e389">Hieronymus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e397">Vera illa necessitudo est, et Christi glutino
              copulata, quam non utilitas rei familiaris, non praesentia tantum corporum, non
              subdola et palpans adulatio, sed Dei timor, et divinarum Scripturarum studia
              conciliant.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e402">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e412" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e404">Hieronymus, in originali <title>super
              Michaeam</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e412">Delicata est amicitia, quae amicorum felicitatem
              et divitias sequitur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e417">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e427" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e419">Bernardus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e427">Habet vera amicitia nonnunquam objurgationem,
              adulationem nunquam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e432">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e442" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e434">Glossa in <title>Ecclesiasticum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e442">Plena et perfecta amicitia inter perfectos
              viros, ejusdemque virtutis, perseverare potest, et ad hanc quibusdam gradibus
              pervenitur. Primus est mundanorum contemptus. Secundus, ne quis se sapientem et
              consultum judicans, sibi quam amico credere malit. Tertius, ut omnia, quae utilia et
              necessaria aestimat, bono charitatis et pacis proponat. Quartus, ut omnino desinat ab
              ira. Quintus, ut iram fratris etiam irrationabilem sedare cupiat: quia alterius
              tristitia perniciosa est, sicut propria, nisi eam, quantum in te est, etiam de fratris
              mente depellas. Postremus gradus est omnium vitiorum peremptorius, ut de hoc mundo
              credas te quotidie migraturum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e448">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e458" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e450">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e458">Qui utilitatis causa assumptus est, tandiu
              placebit, quandiu utilis erit. Hac re florentes amicorum turba circumsidet; circa
              eversos solitudo est, et inde amici fugiunt ubi probantur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e463">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e473" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e465">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e473">Amicum paro, ut habeam pro quo mori possim; ut
              habeam quem in exilium sequar; cujus me morti et opponam, et impendam. Detrahit
              amicitiae majestatem suam, qui illam parat ad bonos casus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-d1e478">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e488" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Rd1e480">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e40249-Qd1e488">Amicos optime res secundae parant; adversae
              certissime probant.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
